\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. L. spinocarpos} (Forskal) Ascherson ex O. Kuntze, {\i Acta Horti Petrop.}{\b  10}: 215 (1887) ({\i Sclerocaryopsis spinocarpos} (Forskal) Brand). Annual, densely appressed-grey-hairy. Stem 5-25 cm, decumbent or erect, branched. Leaves 20-40 × 1-3 mm, linear. Pedicels c. 1 mm, erect. Calyx 3-4 mm in flower, 6-8 mm in fruit. Corolla 3-4 mm; limb infundibuliform, blue. Nutlets 2·5-3 mm, ovoid-trigonous, convex on the upper surface; margin and upper surface with large, irregular, conical spines.{\i  Dry clay soils. S.E. Russia} ({\i Volga delta}). Rs (E).
