\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. L. echinophora} (Pallas) O. Kuntze, {\i op. cit.} 214 (1887) ({\i Heterocaryum echinophorum} (Pallas) Brand). Annual, hispid with erecto-patent hairs often arising from small tubercles. Stem 5-50 cm, erect, often branched. Leaves 15-50 × 1-10 mm, linear to linear-lanceolate, the lower petiolate, the upper sessile. Pedicels up to 5 mm, erect. Calyx c. 2 mm in flower, c. 5 mm in fruit. Corolla 2-2·5 mm; limb infundibuliform, pale blue or whitish. Nutlets unequal in size, the larger 5-7 mm, the smaller 4-5 mm, oblong, attached to the receptacle by their whole length; upper surface flat, sometimes with a row of glochidia down the centre; margin raised, with 1 row of glochidia. {\i Stony places and steppes. • S.E. Russia, W. Kazakhstan.} Rs (E).
