\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. L. marginata} (Bieb.) Gürke in Engler & Prantl,{\i  Natürl. Pflanzenfam.}{\b  4}({\b 3a}): 107 (1895) (incl.{\i  L. patula} (Lehm.) Menyh.,{\i  L. semiglabra} (Ledeb.) Gürke,{\i  L. stricta} (Ledeb.) Gürke, {\i L. tenuis} (Ledeb.) Gürke, {\i Echinospermum patulum} Lehm.). Annual, grey with dense, erecto-patent hairs. Stem 5-70 cm, erect, simple or branched at base. Leaves 20-100 × 2-8 mm, oblong to linear, the lower petiolate, the upper sessile. Pedicels up to 1·5 mm, erect. Calyx 2-3 mm in flower, 3-4 mm in fruit. Corolla 3-4 mm; limb infundibuliform, blue, rarely white. Nutlets 2-4 mm, flattened-trigonous; upper surface smooth or tuberculate; margin with 1 row of glochidia which are dilated, flattened and united at the base.{\i  Dry places. From Hungary and N. Greece to W. Kazakhstan; S.E. Spain; an occasional casual elsewhere.} Bu Gr Hs Hu Rm Rs (W, K, E) *Si.
