\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. L. barbata} (Bieb.) Gürke in Engler & Prantl,{\i  Natürl. Pflanzenfam.}{\b  4}({\b 3a}): 107 (1895) ({\i Echinophorum barbatum} (Bieb.) Lehm.). Annual or biennial, grey with dense, appressed hairs. Stem 10-70 cm, erect, often branched. Leaves 30-70 × 5-8 mm, linear to lanceolate, the lower petiolate, the upper sessile. Pedicels up to 5 mm, erect. Calyx 2-3 mm in flower, c. 4 mm in fruit. Corolla 3-5 mm; limb (3-)5-8 mm in diameter, almost rotate, white or blue. Nutlets 3-4 mm, flattened-trigonous; upper surface minutely tuberculate; margin with 2-3 rows of glochidia which are usually neither dilated nor flattened at the base.{\i  Dry places. S.E. Europe, from S. Albania to E. Ukraine; E. Spain.} Al Bu Hs Rm Rs (W, K, E).
