\pard\f0\fs28 Annual or perennial herbs. Flowers in terminal, ebracteate cymes. Calyx lobed to below the middle, accrescent. Corolla blue, infundibuliform to campanulate or rotate with short tube and with papillose or hairy scales in the throat. Stamens included, inserted about middle of tube. Style included; stigma capitate. Nutlets trigonous, erect, smooth, with a small attachment area, often stipitate.
