\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. T. peduncularis} (Trev.) Bentham ex Baker & S. Moore,{\i  Jour. Linn. Soc. London} ({\i Bot}.) {\b 17}: 384 (1879). Annual; stems 5-20 cm, erect or ascending, branched, scabrid-pubescent. Leaves 7-20 × 5-8 cm, spathulate to oblong or lanceolate, greyish with appressed hairs. Cymes secund, very lax in fruit; pedicels 3-6 mm in fruit and patent and thickened at the apex. Calyx c. 1 mm in flower, 2-2·5 mm in fruit, greyish with appressed hairs; lobes ovate-oblong, acute. Corolla c. 1·5 mm; limb 2-3 mm in diameter, bright blue, lobed to c. ¾ ; lobes ovate, obtuse. Nutlets c. 1 mm, minutely hairy on upper surface or glabrous. {\i S.E. Russia} ({\i near Astrakhan'}). Rs(E). ({\i C. & E. Asia}.)
