\pard\f0\fs28 Annual, biennial or perennial herbs. Flowers solitary and axillary or in mostly terminal, bracteate or ebracteate cymes. Calyx lobed to the base, accrescent. Corolla blue or white, subrotate or almost campanulate, with short tube and 5 prominent, saccate invaginations in the throat. Stamens included, inserted at about middle of tube. Style included; stigma capitate. Nutlets depressed-globose, smooth, sometimes hairy, winged, with the wing erect or incurved to form an umbilicus, attached to the receptacle for almost their whole length.
